        "In order to access the root data, you first need to mount your google drive containing the csv file using\n",
        "```from google.colab import drive\n",
        "drive.mount('/content/gdrive')\n",
        "```\n",
        "Before accessing the data, we need to import two tools to assist us in data filtration. These tools are called numpy and pandas, the ensuring code defines them as \"np\" and \"pd\" to allow for ease of understanding.\n",
        "```\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Once colab now has access and the data tools are imported, we can use them to access the data within the google drive. To do this, I used\n",
