        "## Isolating the United States Data\n",
        "\n",
        "Now that I have a set of data with just the United States, I can create a second data set with only this data.\n",
        "\n",
        "To do this, I use `USAsubset = meow[meow[\"iso_code\"] == \"USA\"].copy()`\n",
        "\n",
        "This code creates a new data set called \"USAsubset\" that contains *only* the data about the US. Defining this allows me to use this new data set without have to filter my original data every time.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PSG_TkIEgUtS"
      }
