        "## Further Filtration\n",
        "\n",
        "Now that I have my data of just the United States, I can filter the data further by choosing one variable to focus on.\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "USAco2 = USAsubset.loc[:,[\"year\",\"co2_growth_prct\"]]\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "This code looks through my new data set I just made called \"USAsubset\" and cuts it down to just data on the variable \"co2_growth_prct\".\n",
        "\n",
        "After it finds the data, it creates a third data set called \"USAco2\" with just United States data and just co2 growth percentage. Now I have my final instance of narrowed data that I can use for visualization."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Q3c0H0FlgYKj"
      }
